I'd almost tend to agree with Laoke - when I first heard about these changes, I thought it was a joke, because each change in and of itself is a big enough change to make people bitch; wrap them up all in one package like this, and the bitching will be increased exponentially. <br>
<br>
While I'm not real upset by these changes, I can see how each of the affected classes would be. The issues VI is addressing are valid issues that people have brought up in the past. But you don't fix things after saying repeatedly that you wouldn't (Manaburn), or after people have worked their entire strategy for particular mobs using a certain method (Modrods), or after it's been the same way for 4 years since the release of the game (Complete Heal). You fix things as soon as you can, you don't leave them alone so long that they become features, so that people become used to them and come to depend on them, then change it all and leave your customers feeling like they've had something taken away.<br>
<br>
Like I said, I may not be real upset by any of these changes, but if they do go through, I'll strongly consider not even buying PoP if this is how VI is going to handle things. Is there anyone besides me that can't wait for Blizzard's World of Warcraft? <p><a target="New" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10932"><img src="http://members.rogers.com/maxwellg/khael2.jpg" alt="Drawn by Saraquael" border=0></a>
